Packages that use cat
Package Description
cat
Package that contains BigCat, Cat and CatAdmirer BigCat is a super class of Lynx, which is in a different package cat.Species and will be used to demonstrate what variables of a particular access type can be accessed from other classes in different package To see video tutorial for this section of code Video tutorial For all 177 videos, which cover all the topics in this course go to Complete Course Video Tutorial
cat.species
package that contains Lynx and will be used to show which variables of different access levels can and cannot be accessed from a different class that in a different package that inherits from this class, in our case the BigCat To see video tutorial for this section of code Video tutorial For all 177 videos, which cover all the topics in this course go to Complete Course Video Tutorial

    Class Description
    Cat
    Abstract class Cat means you can't create an instance of this class, you can have an abstract reference to concrete subclass of Cat, such as Lion.

    public class means it is available to all other classes and can create a BigCat Object in all other classes.
